WEBVTT

00:03.625 --> 00:07.917
[FOOTSTEPS]

00:14.583 --> 00:17.041
[CLICKING]

00:33.500 --> 00:36.500
[BUZZING]

00:36.500 --> 00:37.917
[DOOR CREAKS]

00:41.917 --> 00:43.291
[DOOR CLOSES]

00:44.500 --> 00:46.375
[BEEPING]

00:49.250 --> 00:50.458
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

00:53.500 --> 00:54.792
Hi, Professor Wilder?

00:56.250 --> 00:58.208
Okay, David, then.

00:58.500 --> 00:59.750
Feels weird.

01:00.166 --> 01:02.708
Um, so I'm done here.

01:02.708 --> 01:04.625
Is-- is it okay
if I still stop by?

01:07.041 --> 01:09.375
Okay, well, I'm just about
to get on the "T", so...

01:10.000 --> 01:11.625
I'll see you in a bit.

01:12.000 --> 01:13.500
[BEEPING]

01:13.500 --> 01:14.667
Bye.

01:30.208 --> 01:34.834
-[SECOND SET OF FOOTSTEPS]
-[EXHALING]

01:40.417 --> 01:41.583
[CIGARETTE BURNING]

01:44.000 --> 01:45.208
[EXHALING]

01:46.583 --> 01:48.750
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

01:48.750 --> 01:49.959
Hey.

01:51.083 --> 01:52.250
Hey.

01:52.250 --> 01:54.291
I didn't mean to scare you
or anything.

01:54.291 --> 01:55.500
Well, you did, so...

01:55.917 --> 01:57.166
So, where you headin'?

01:57.166 --> 01:57.917
Home.

01:58.291 --> 02:00.250
-Oh yeah? Where's home?
-Uh, none of your business.

02:00.250 --> 02:02.041
Ooh, snotty. I like-- Hey.

02:02.834 --> 02:04.417
I'm not gonna mug you
or anything,

02:04.417 --> 02:05.917
if that's what
you're worried about.

02:06.583 --> 02:07.375
Good to know.

02:07.625 --> 02:09.458
And I'm not about
to force myself on you.

02:09.458 --> 02:10.458
[LAUGHS]

02:10.458 --> 02:12.500
I can get my own dates.
Thank you very much.

02:13.500 --> 02:14.875
Don't look so relieved.

02:14.875 --> 02:16.166
As far as potential rapists go--

02:16.166 --> 02:17.333
Look, I don't mean
to be rude, but--

02:17.333 --> 02:19.000
Hey, hey, I know
what you're thinking.

02:19.625 --> 02:20.959
You're thinking,
who is this guy?

02:20.959 --> 02:23.917
Why is he violating
my envelope of space?

02:25.583 --> 02:26.417
Well...

02:26.417 --> 02:27.708
Truth is, I was wondering

02:27.708 --> 02:29.667
if you had any money
that I could borrow.

02:30.125 --> 02:31.166
No.

02:31.625 --> 02:33.250
No? You're not even
gonna think about it?

02:33.250 --> 02:34.500
I've thought about it,
and I said no.

02:34.500 --> 02:35.625
See, this-- This...

02:36.041 --> 02:37.458
Is the problem with the world.

02:38.166 --> 02:39.458
I mean, you put yourself
out there.

02:39.458 --> 02:40.917
Y-- you make yourself
vulnerable.

02:41.458 --> 02:43.250
They just shoot you down
without a second thought.

02:43.250 --> 02:45.500
Listen. I'm sorry.
I don't have any money, okay?

02:45.959 --> 02:47.166
And seriously,
you're scaring me,

02:47.166 --> 02:48.708
and I ju-- I just
want to get home.

02:50.583 --> 02:53.375
Okay. Fair enough.
I'm sorry for the hassle.

02:55.333 --> 02:56.500
Want me to walk you home?

02:56.500 --> 02:57.417
No.

02:57.417 --> 02:58.708
That's understandable,
but you know,

02:58.708 --> 03:00.166
you should be careful,
sweetheart.

03:00.792 --> 03:01.625
I mean, it's late.

03:02.333 --> 03:05.250
Next guy you come across,
he might not be as nice as me.

03:06.458 --> 03:08.667
[SIRENS]

03:08.667 --> 03:09.875
Be good.

03:12.291 --> 03:13.458
Actually, you know what?

03:14.875 --> 03:16.333
Uh, I've given this
some thought,

03:16.333 --> 03:19.083
and I'd rather if you
did lend me that money.

03:25.625 --> 03:26.834
How's that work for you?

03:32.125 --> 03:35.542
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

04:11.792 --> 04:14.083
What? You think
I'm just gonna let you walk off

04:14.083 --> 04:15.834
once the handgun's
made an appearance?

04:16.250 --> 04:17.458
Give me a break.

04:18.750 --> 04:19.666
Let's go over here.

04:23.500 --> 04:25.333
Come on. Just give me
what you got.

04:25.333 --> 04:27.208
I assure you this will all end
reasonably well.

04:27.208 --> 04:28.917
Look, I don't have
anything to give you.

04:28.917 --> 04:31.291
First of all, hon,
you just walked out of an ATM.

04:31.542 --> 04:34.250
Secondly, rich little
college girl like you...

04:34.583 --> 04:35.792
Where do you go?

04:36.250 --> 04:37.375
Harvard?

04:37.375 --> 04:38.250
Or Wellesley?

04:38.834 --> 04:39.750
Worthington.

04:39.750 --> 04:41.542
Ha ha. See?
That's very nice.

04:41.542 --> 04:43.417
It doesn't make me any less
broke at the moment.

04:43.417 --> 04:44.959
Oh, what?
Are you gettin' scared?

04:46.583 --> 04:47.875
You don't have...
Don't be scared.

04:48.917 --> 04:50.875
That's easy for you to say.
You're holding the gun.

04:51.417 --> 04:54.125
Okay, be scared,
but just so you know,

04:54.125 --> 04:56.333
I really don't have any
intention of using it.

04:57.458 --> 04:59.125
Right. This from the guy
who 5 minutes ago said

04:59.125 --> 05:00.333
he had no intention
of mugging me.

05:00.333 --> 05:01.917
-Just trying to put you at ease.
-Maybe you should

05:01.917 --> 05:03.667
have thought twice about,
I don't know, mugging me.

05:03.667 --> 05:04.917
What's done is done.

05:05.208 --> 05:06.667
Water under the bridge
and whatnot.

05:07.125 --> 05:08.834
I think we're gonna
have to get past it.

05:08.834 --> 05:10.166
I mean, if we're gonna have
a successful

05:10.166 --> 05:12.041
mugger/muggee relationship here.

05:14.125 --> 05:15.208
Don't you?

05:16.041 --> 05:17.959
Is there any chance that
that gun may accidentally

05:17.959 --> 05:19.125
go off in your pants?

05:19.625 --> 05:20.959
Because that
would be really great.

05:20.959 --> 05:21.667
You know what?

05:22.041 --> 05:24.125
You, young lady, are a wise-ass,
you know that?

05:24.750 --> 05:26.667
And I may just have
to shoot you yet.

05:26.667 --> 05:27.667
[GUN COCKS]

05:28.208 --> 05:29.083
Let's go.

05:30.917 --> 05:32.250
Gimme what you got.

05:35.333 --> 05:36.208
Come on.

05:39.625 --> 05:40.875
Twenty bucks, you scored.

05:41.375 --> 05:42.667
Oh, come on. You gotta
be kidding me.

05:42.667 --> 05:43.917
This is barely bus fare.

05:45.333 --> 05:47.625
Guess I left my wads of hundreds
in another jeans.

05:47.625 --> 05:49.959
Well, you got a cell phone
or something.

05:50.500 --> 05:51.500
Right?

05:51.500 --> 05:52.333
No.

05:52.834 --> 05:54.458
-Telling me the truth?
-Yes.

05:55.375 --> 05:57.000
So it's okay if I pat you down?

05:57.375 --> 05:59.375
'Cause that might be
kind of fun.

06:03.458 --> 06:04.250
Oh, cool.

06:04.959 --> 06:07.000
Yeah, I hope you get
a decent signal in prison.

06:07.000 --> 06:09.333
Tone. Watch it.

06:11.834 --> 06:12.917
Oh, wow. This is a nice one.

06:12.917 --> 06:14.834
This is, like, really light.

06:15.250 --> 06:16.166
Aesthetically pleasing.

06:16.458 --> 06:18.667
Can I, uh, go on the internet
with this thing?

06:18.917 --> 06:20.333
[GRUNTS]

06:22.542 --> 06:26.667
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

06:27.792 --> 06:29.250
Aah! Aah!

06:31.959 --> 06:34.959
[LAUGHS]
That was not cool.

06:35.708 --> 06:36.959
-Sorry.
-Are you crazy?

06:37.291 --> 06:39.000
How do you know I'm not
gonna kill you for that?

06:39.375 --> 06:41.250
Is that what you're gonna do?
You gonna kill me?

06:41.250 --> 06:43.250
I don't know.
I haven't made up my mind yet.

06:43.750 --> 06:46.250
Well, in the meantime,
get the hell off of me!

06:46.250 --> 06:47.708
[LAUGHS]

06:48.375 --> 06:50.959
[HEAVY BREATHING]

06:58.458 --> 06:59.750
Give me the damn cell phone.

07:02.083 --> 07:03.083
What is your name?

07:03.083 --> 07:04.250
That's none of your business.

07:04.542 --> 07:05.375
[GUN COCKS]

07:06.083 --> 07:07.041
What is your name?

07:08.208 --> 07:09.250
Joey.

07:09.750 --> 07:11.583
Joey. I like Joey.

07:12.166 --> 07:14.375
I've always liked
boys names for girls.

07:15.166 --> 07:16.291
It's cute.

07:16.291 --> 07:17.875
My parents will be thrilled.
Are we done here?

07:17.875 --> 07:19.041
What do you think, Joey?

07:19.417 --> 07:20.917
Look, you have my money
and my cell phone.

07:20.917 --> 07:21.917
What else do you want?

07:23.667 --> 07:25.000
Well, you're gonna
have to kill me then.

07:25.000 --> 07:26.875
[LAUGHS]
Don't flatter yourself.

07:27.166 --> 07:29.417
You got a credit card?
ATM card?

07:29.875 --> 07:31.417
One of those jazzy
little check cards

07:31.417 --> 07:32.917
that are all the rage
these days?

07:33.458 --> 07:34.625
And if you have it,
give it to me.

07:34.625 --> 07:35.458
Don't screw around.

07:35.917 --> 07:37.125
Give it to me.
Unless, of course,

07:37.125 --> 07:38.375
you want me to pat you down.

07:40.834 --> 07:42.125
Thank you.

07:42.125 --> 07:43.041
[SIGHS]

07:43.041 --> 07:44.458
Well, credit card's
fairly useless.

07:44.458 --> 07:46.500
You'll just cancel that
the first chance you get.

07:47.667 --> 07:49.000
Unless of course, I kill you.

07:50.333 --> 07:51.542
Kidding.

07:53.458 --> 07:54.417
Oh! ATM card.

07:54.792 --> 07:56.834
Okay. Here's what
we're gonna do.

07:57.333 --> 08:00.083
We're gonna go down to the
little ATM vestibule over here.

08:00.083 --> 08:01.333
You're gonna take out
all your money,

08:01.333 --> 08:02.542
and you're gonna give it to me.

08:03.125 --> 08:05.125
I only have $27 in my account.

08:05.417 --> 08:08.291
I don't buy that for a second,
Joey who goes to Worthington.

08:08.291 --> 08:09.291
Well, it's true.

08:11.208 --> 08:12.375
Prove it.

08:13.625 --> 08:14.875
[DOOR BUZZING]

08:16.375 --> 08:18.000
[FOOTSTEPS ECHO]

08:21.834 --> 08:23.583
-[ATM BEEPS]
-All right. Work your magic.

08:26.166 --> 08:27.166
I won't look.

08:29.583 --> 08:31.208
[ATM BEEPING]

08:33.667 --> 08:34.875
Forty-seven bucks?

08:34.875 --> 08:36.625
I get kicked in the gut
for 47 bucks?

08:36.625 --> 08:37.958
No. Don't forget the cell phone.

08:39.082 --> 08:40.207
What about your savings?

08:40.582 --> 08:42.457
[ATM BEEPS]

08:44.500 --> 08:45.417
Disco.

08:45.417 --> 08:46.625
[ATM BEEPS]

08:46.625 --> 08:47.583
[LAUGHS]

08:47.959 --> 08:48.875
Well, don't worry, sweetie.

08:49.291 --> 08:51.667
I'm sure Daddy'll cut you
a check first thing Monday.

08:52.458 --> 08:54.834
Oh, you so want to punch me in
the face right now, don't you?

08:55.542 --> 08:57.000
I mean, I understand,
I really do,

08:57.000 --> 08:58.500
but I got bills to pay.

08:59.125 --> 09:01.166
Sorry if that's slightly more
important to me than you buying

09:01.166 --> 09:03.041
yourself a new pair
of Manano Blahniks.

09:03.041 --> 09:04.708
Did you ever think
of getting a job?

09:04.708 --> 09:06.041
Hey. I have a job.

09:06.041 --> 09:07.000
Oh, yeah? Doing what?

09:07.000 --> 09:08.166
Not that it's any
of your business,

09:08.166 --> 09:10.375
but I guess you could say
I'm in sales.

09:10.375 --> 09:13.208
-Let me guess. Telemarketing?
-Ha. Funny.

09:13.208 --> 09:14.708
More like pharmaceuticals.

09:15.250 --> 09:16.708
Oh, you're a drug dealer.

09:16.708 --> 09:18.041
Oh, you say that
with such disgust.

09:18.041 --> 09:19.542
Oh, I didn't know
your industry was worthy

09:19.542 --> 09:21.041
of such honor and respect.

09:22.458 --> 09:24.250
You know, I've got some clients
that go to Worthington.

09:24.250 --> 09:26.875
Hmm. You should stop by
sometime. We can catch up.

09:28.500 --> 09:33.375
You know, call me crazy,
but I like you, Joey.

09:33.750 --> 09:36.542
I mean, except for that little
Kung Fu kick out there,

09:36.875 --> 09:39.000
you've made this experience
a very pleasant one.

09:39.500 --> 09:42.041
A lot of people, they would
have pissed their pants by now,

09:42.583 --> 09:46.708
but you, you held it together,
kept your sense of humor.

09:47.041 --> 09:48.250
[SIGHS]
You know what?

09:48.250 --> 09:49.792
I'm not even gonna hold that
violent little outburst

09:49.792 --> 09:50.834
of yours against you.

09:51.792 --> 09:52.708
Gee, thanks.

09:53.583 --> 09:55.708
I mean, another time,
another place...

09:55.959 --> 09:56.959
What?

09:57.417 --> 09:59.166
You and me might make
a scorching couple.

10:00.500 --> 10:02.083
You must be dipping
into your supply.

10:02.083 --> 10:03.458
You cannot tell me
that you don't find me

10:03.458 --> 10:04.417
the slightest bit attractive.

10:04.417 --> 10:05.750
Oh, yeah. You're a real catch.

10:05.750 --> 10:06.208
[LAUGHS]

10:06.875 --> 10:08.250
Except for maybe that little
part about you being

10:08.250 --> 10:09.000
a lowlife criminal.

10:09.583 --> 10:11.625
Oh, yeah. That's original.
Let's pick on the drug dealer.

10:11.625 --> 10:12.500
That's an easy target.

10:13.834 --> 10:15.959
-Can I go now?
-No, you can't.

10:16.542 --> 10:18.291
I have another question for you.

10:19.083 --> 10:20.667
[SIGHS]
What?

10:23.417 --> 10:24.500
Are you a virgin?

10:26.291 --> 10:28.750
Could you be any more
of a dick right now?

10:28.750 --> 10:31.166
Yeah. I could kill ya,
or worse, even.

10:31.458 --> 10:32.583
Uh, uh, uh, uh!

10:33.208 --> 10:34.083
Just screwing with ya.

10:34.625 --> 10:37.000
I do have another
question though, if that's okay.

10:37.000 --> 10:38.083
What?

10:38.792 --> 10:41.417
-Okay...you're a girl.
-Yes.

10:41.750 --> 10:43.959
-Do you have a boyfriend?
-No.

10:43.959 --> 10:45.458
Well, have you ever
had a boyfriend?

10:45.458 --> 10:48.041
-Yes.
-Okay, so, if you

10:48.041 --> 10:50.583
had a boyfriend right now
and you were mad at him,

10:50.875 --> 10:54.250
what might be the best way
to get back in your good graces?

10:55.959 --> 10:57.166
Somebody actually dates you?

10:57.166 --> 10:59.417
Hey, somebody
actually married me.

10:59.417 --> 11:00.291
[SCOFFS]

11:00.291 --> 11:01.458
Sorry to hear that,
for her sake.

11:01.458 --> 11:02.875
Yeah, well, somebody's
gotta fall in love

11:02.875 --> 11:04.417
with the drug dealers
of the world.

11:04.792 --> 11:07.500
I mean, are we not human, Joey?
Are we no less divine?

11:07.500 --> 11:09.750
I guess you're right.
Even Hitler had a girlfriend.

11:09.750 --> 11:11.333
Exactly. Eva Braun,

11:11.875 --> 11:13.291
and she was one smitten kitten.

11:14.417 --> 11:15.834
I can't believe
I'm even participating

11:15.834 --> 11:19.125
in this conversation,
but...did you ever think

11:19.125 --> 11:20.542
of getting her something?

11:21.375 --> 11:22.834
Uh, flowers?

11:23.083 --> 11:24.083
Well, how pissed is she?

11:24.333 --> 11:26.000
-Well, she's really pissed.
-Nature of the crime?

11:26.000 --> 11:28.000
My dabblings in
the underworld and whatnot.

11:28.000 --> 11:30.166
Oh, you're gonna have to do
much better than flowers.

11:31.500 --> 11:32.583
That's a nice jacket.

11:35.166 --> 11:37.083
-Thanks.
-Where'd you get it?

11:37.708 --> 11:38.875
[SCOFFS]

11:39.333 --> 11:41.250
It was a gift, I think.

11:42.959 --> 11:43.959
Can I have it?

11:44.458 --> 11:45.959
Are you kidding me? No.

11:46.834 --> 11:48.000
Uh, uh, uh!

11:49.834 --> 11:51.250
Wasn't really a question.

11:52.708 --> 11:54.208
You're stealing my coat?

11:54.708 --> 11:56.333
I can't believe you're
stealing my coat!

11:56.333 --> 11:57.917
What difference does it make
at this point?

11:57.917 --> 11:59.708
-I don't think it really--
-It's freezing outside!

11:59.708 --> 12:01.000
Yeah, it sure is.

12:01.250 --> 12:03.000
Tch tch. That's not my problem.

12:03.792 --> 12:05.000
-[SIGHS]
-Gimme the coat.

12:06.125 --> 12:07.250
Oh, my god.

12:09.500 --> 12:11.333
Oh, wow. This is
a really nice one.

12:12.625 --> 12:15.125
Well, this is just her size.
She's gonna love this.

12:15.375 --> 12:17.333
-Thank you.
-Glad to be of service.

12:18.375 --> 12:21.166
Well, I guess this is goodbye.

12:23.959 --> 12:25.750
Oh, by the way,

12:25.750 --> 12:27.375
you can go to the cops
and all that,

12:27.375 --> 12:28.834
but trust me,
it's a waste of time.

12:28.834 --> 12:31.500
-Thanks for the tip.
-Yep. Okay, well...

12:37.333 --> 12:38.208
You take care.

12:41.333 --> 12:45.166
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

12:53.417 --> 12:56.917
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

13:10.792 --> 13:12.208
[WHISTLE]

13:14.291 --> 13:16.250
-[TIRES SQUEAKING]
-[CAR HORN]

13:17.375 --> 13:19.125
-[GLASS SHATTERS]
-[THUD]

13:27.542 --> 13:31.542
-[ENGINE REVVING]
-[TIRES SQUEALING]

13:39.458 --> 13:41.250
[CLICKING]

13:46.083 --> 13:48.542
[CLICKING]

13:57.083 --> 14:00.917
[FOOTSTEPS]

14:39.417 --> 14:40.333
[GASP]

14:40.333 --> 14:42.875
[COUGHS]
Don't.

14:42.875 --> 14:43.959
I'm calling for help.

14:43.959 --> 14:45.333
Yeah, right. You're
gonna call the cops.

14:45.333 --> 14:46.708
Of course I am, but
I'll ask 'em to bring

14:46.708 --> 14:47.583
a Band-Aid or two.

14:47.583 --> 14:48.917
-[COUGHS]
-You need help.

14:48.917 --> 14:49.792
I'm fine.

14:50.041 --> 14:52.041
Yeah, you look like hell.
I thought you were dead.

14:52.041 --> 14:54.250
Yeah, well, I'm speaking.
I'm clearly not dead.

14:54.250 --> 14:56.875
-Yet.
-Give me it. Give me it.

14:56.875 --> 14:58.041
[GRUNTS]

15:01.834 --> 15:02.875
[COUGHS]

15:03.750 --> 15:04.625
Hey!

15:06.375 --> 15:07.750
You stay or die.

15:08.792 --> 15:11.708
-You're not gonna shoot me.
-I'm not? You sure about that?

15:11.708 --> 15:12.917
Yeah. You like me, remember?

15:12.917 --> 15:14.417
I've made this experience
a very pleasant one.

15:14.417 --> 15:15.875
Yeah, well, that's all
well and good, hon,

15:15.875 --> 15:16.750
but I ain't going to jail.

15:16.750 --> 15:18.750
No, you're going
to the hospital.

15:19.750 --> 15:20.667
Then jail.

15:21.834 --> 15:22.917
[GUN COCKS]

15:23.792 --> 15:25.250
Not if I have any say in it.

15:29.417 --> 15:30.208
Okay.

15:33.500 --> 15:36.625
I'm gonna walk over there,
pick up my phone,

15:36.625 --> 15:39.875
and if it still works,
I'm gonna dial 911,

15:39.875 --> 15:41.542
and I'm gonna get you
an ambulance.

15:43.041 --> 15:45.875
You want to shoot me,
go right ahead.

15:53.250 --> 15:54.375
-[CLICK]
-Aah!

15:54.625 --> 15:57.500
-[GRUNTS]
-It was never loaded?

15:58.125 --> 16:00.208
I never actually got around
to buying bullets.

16:00.583 --> 16:02.041
Looks pretty cool, though, huh?

16:03.875 --> 16:05.333
-[COUGHS]
-I'm calling.

16:05.708 --> 16:08.667
Hey, come on. Just go home.
I'm fine.

16:08.667 --> 16:10.333
-Yeah. You look fine.
-Wait.

16:11.417 --> 16:12.375
I'm fine.

16:17.333 --> 16:19.125
Fine.
[GRUNTS]

16:19.125 --> 16:22.250
[COUGHS]
[GRUNTS]

16:23.542 --> 16:25.750
-How about that ambulance?
-[CHUCKLES]

16:28.417 --> 16:30.834
Sure. Why the hell not?

16:37.417 --> 16:38.834
[CLICKING]

16:40.125 --> 16:43.166
-They're on their way.
-Cops, too?

16:43.834 --> 16:45.500
-Of course.
-[LAUGHS]

16:45.500 --> 16:46.917
How happy are you right now?

16:46.917 --> 16:49.834
Oh, yeah. This is exactly
how I like to spend my nights.

16:49.834 --> 16:51.750
Well, you can't deny
the poetry of it all.

16:52.166 --> 16:53.500
What are you talking about?

16:53.917 --> 16:55.458
You think this was an accident?

16:56.708 --> 16:58.500
This was no accident,
sweetheart.

17:01.542 --> 17:02.708
I mean, I get hit by that car

17:02.708 --> 17:04.416
after I do something
crappy to you.

17:05.541 --> 17:07.165
Kicked in the ass by karma.

17:07.708 --> 17:08.959
Who'd have thunk it?
[COUGHS]

17:12.165 --> 17:14.625
-Is there something I can do?
-[COUGHS]

17:16.165 --> 17:17.416
You have any heroin?

17:18.834 --> 17:20.083
Not on me, no.

17:20.083 --> 17:21.625
Then shut up
and leave me alone.

17:21.625 --> 17:22.916
Tone. Watch it.

17:30.000 --> 17:31.000
[COUGHS]

17:31.875 --> 17:33.583
[GRUNTS]

17:35.000 --> 17:37.333
-Do you smoke?
-No.

17:37.917 --> 17:39.250
My mom, lung cancer.

17:39.792 --> 17:41.583
-Swore I never would.
-[CHUCKLES]

17:43.041 --> 17:43.917
What's so funny?

17:44.333 --> 17:46.959
My old man. Lung cancer, too.

17:47.625 --> 17:48.834
Didn't stop me, though.

17:50.000 --> 17:52.417
So, is that what you deal?
Heroin?

17:53.041 --> 17:57.375
No. "X," mostly.
You ever try it?

17:57.750 --> 17:59.417
No. I'm not really into drugs.

17:59.792 --> 18:01.125
Yeah, I don't like 'em, either.

18:01.708 --> 18:03.542
They just really
seem to like me.

18:03.542 --> 18:04.667
Can I ask you a question?

18:05.000 --> 18:06.333
Does it look like
I'm going anywhere?

18:06.792 --> 18:09.542
You're a drug dealer. Fairly
lucrative profession, right?

18:10.834 --> 18:12.959
So, why do you go around
terrorizing college girls

18:12.959 --> 18:14.125
in the middle of the night?

18:15.458 --> 18:17.041
Well, Joey,

18:17.708 --> 18:19.500
the industry in which I toil,

18:19.875 --> 18:22.250
it goes through
periodic dry spells.

18:22.708 --> 18:24.500
This just happens
to be one of them.

18:25.667 --> 18:26.583
Plus, I have a very

18:26.583 --> 18:28.917
high-maintenance wench
of a wife.

18:31.083 --> 18:33.583
How does the little lady
feel about your line of work?

18:33.583 --> 18:35.375
She's not a big fan, actually.

18:36.208 --> 18:38.750
In fact, she finally kicked my
ass out last month.

18:39.542 --> 18:42.125
I'm trying to worm my way back
into her heart ever since.

18:43.583 --> 18:47.125
-Do you want me to call her?
-No.

18:48.458 --> 18:51.083
Well, I'm sure she'd probably
like to know about this.

18:51.083 --> 18:53.667
Yeah, well, I don't want her
to know, okay?

18:57.625 --> 18:59.458
[GRUNTS]
[GROANS]

19:01.458 --> 19:04.125
[GROANS]
[COUGHS]

19:05.917 --> 19:07.041
How'd you guys meet?

19:08.333 --> 19:09.542
[GROANS]

19:11.625 --> 19:15.000
High school.
Tenth grade.

19:16.291 --> 19:17.875
She liked me.

19:19.458 --> 19:21.083
I never even saw it.

19:22.000 --> 19:24.250
Never gave her
the time of day.

19:25.291 --> 19:28.875
Then one day,
she smiled at me.

19:30.375 --> 19:32.000
No particular reason.

19:33.291 --> 19:34.834
It was the end of me.

19:37.166 --> 19:40.208
It's funny how things
are always shifting like that.

19:42.625 --> 19:44.792
One day, you have
the upper hand,

19:46.041 --> 19:50.208
you're in control,
and...the next,

19:50.208 --> 19:52.458
you're totally
at somebody's mercy.

19:55.083 --> 19:57.500
Kind of like me and you.
[COUGHS]

19:58.166 --> 20:00.375
-[COUGHS]
-There is no me and you.

20:02.917 --> 20:04.542
Can I ask you something?

20:08.417 --> 20:10.166
Does it look like
I'm going anywhere?

20:10.542 --> 20:12.583
Why are you being
so nice to me?

20:18.125 --> 20:19.208
It doesn't take a doctor

20:19.208 --> 20:20.708
to know that you're
in pretty bad shape.

20:20.708 --> 20:22.458
But most people probably

20:22.458 --> 20:24.291
would've left me
for dead by now.

20:27.000 --> 20:29.083
Well, most people don't want to
see you put in jail as badly

20:29.083 --> 20:31.083
-as I do.
-[CHUCKLES]

20:32.458 --> 20:33.542
That's a good point.

20:37.083 --> 20:38.875
My father used to deal drugs.

20:39.250 --> 20:41.625
[LAUGHS]
Really?

20:43.708 --> 20:46.125
That's right. I think I saw him
at a union meeting once.

20:46.917 --> 20:49.166
-How's he doing?
-He went to prison.

20:50.458 --> 20:51.708
He's there right now.

20:55.333 --> 20:58.083
My whole life, I was
trying to figure out

20:58.083 --> 21:00.333
why someone would do
something like that.

21:01.208 --> 21:04.291
He had a wife,
two daughters that thought

21:04.291 --> 21:05.875
he was a damn superhero.

21:11.917 --> 21:12.917
[SIRENS]

21:12.917 --> 21:15.000
Maybe that's why
I'm being so nice to you.

21:19.542 --> 21:22.417
-I want to know why.
-[SIRENS]

21:40.542 --> 21:42.917
[VOICES CHATTERING]

21:48.625 --> 21:50.834
-You okay, miss?
-Oh, yeah. I'm fine.

21:51.667 --> 21:53.792
So, this guy mugs you,
then gets hit by a car?

21:54.333 --> 21:55.792
Those are the cliff notes, yeah.

21:56.417 --> 21:59.583
Wow. That happened more often,
I'd be out of a job.

22:00.959 --> 22:03.375
Come on. You should take a ride
to the hospital.

22:04.083 --> 22:07.166
-Have 'em take a look at you.
-It's okay. I just...

22:08.834 --> 22:10.333
I just want to go...

22:12.291 --> 22:16.166
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

22:27.875 --> 22:30.291
[MACHINES BEEPING]

22:39.000 --> 22:41.000
DOCTOR: Well, all's well
that ends well, Miss Potter.

22:42.125 --> 22:43.417
-I'm okay?
-Yeah, you're fine.

22:43.417 --> 22:45.166
You're fine. You were in shock,
which, given what you've

22:45.166 --> 22:47.000
been through this evening,
is understandable.

22:47.500 --> 22:48.750
Have you spoken
to the police?

22:49.542 --> 22:50.792
Well, go home
and get some sleep.

22:51.083 --> 22:53.834
-Anybody we can call for you?
-No. I'll be fine.

22:54.250 --> 22:55.625
Okay, then, young lady.

22:56.166 --> 22:57.500
You take care of yourself.

22:58.667 --> 23:00.125
-Uh, excuse me.
-Mm-hmm?

23:01.875 --> 23:03.208
How's the guy?

23:03.208 --> 23:05.208
Oh, the creep who mugged you?
Oh, he's great.

23:05.208 --> 23:06.875
He's in surgery right now.

23:06.875 --> 23:08.417
Lots of internal bleeding.

23:11.291 --> 23:15.500
[MACHINES BEEPING]

23:32.166 --> 23:35.834
-[VOICES CHATTERING]
-[PHONES RINGING]

23:47.333 --> 23:48.458
Hi, sweetheart.

23:48.458 --> 23:50.500
Hi. Where's your mom
and dad?

23:51.542 --> 23:53.041
You have pretty hair.

23:53.041 --> 23:55.792
Aw, thank you.
You have pretty hair, too.

23:56.417 --> 23:57.750
Why don't we go see
if we can find

23:57.750 --> 23:58.917
your mom and dad, huh?

23:59.542 --> 24:00.500
Okay.

24:02.417 --> 24:03.417
Mama!

24:04.500 --> 24:06.250
She has brown hair, blue eyes.

24:06.250 --> 24:07.875
-She has to be here somewhere.
-Mama!

24:08.375 --> 24:11.917
Oh, baby. I'm so sorry.
Mommy got distracted.

24:12.750 --> 24:14.041
Thank you so much.

24:14.333 --> 24:15.250
No problem.

24:15.917 --> 24:16.875
She's a cute one.

24:16.875 --> 24:18.125
Yeah, she's
a cute one, all right,

24:18.125 --> 24:20.166
especially when she
wanders off like that.

24:20.959 --> 24:22.083
Thanks again.

24:22.083 --> 24:23.291
No problem.

24:25.041 --> 24:27.375
Could you do me
an enormous favor?

24:29.166 --> 24:31.500
-I'm sorry. Forget about it.
-No. What?

24:32.125 --> 24:34.041
Could you maybe
sit with her for a minute?

24:34.041 --> 24:35.667
-I'm trying to find my husband.
-Absolutely.

24:35.667 --> 24:37.667
[SIGHS]
You're a doll. Thank you.

24:38.959 --> 24:40.000
Come on.

24:49.750 --> 24:52.125
It's way past my bedtime.

24:52.375 --> 24:54.458
I know. You must be tired.

24:54.750 --> 24:58.041
Yeah. My daddy's sick.

24:58.583 --> 25:00.375
I'm sorry about that.

25:01.125 --> 25:04.333
Sometimes he takes me
to the movies.

25:04.333 --> 25:06.667
Yeah? That's nice of him.

25:06.667 --> 25:09.458
Yeah. He's not feeling so good.

25:09.792 --> 25:11.458
He got hit by a car.

25:16.000 --> 25:17.500
[SIGHS]
[CHUCKLES]

25:17.959 --> 25:19.500
-Here.
-JOEY: Oh, thank you.

25:20.959 --> 25:22.875
I-I can't thank you enough.

25:22.875 --> 25:24.166
Oh, it's my pleasure.

25:24.667 --> 25:26.792
I just hate the way
they look at me, you know?

25:27.208 --> 25:29.333
Can't she just
take care of her kid?

25:31.708 --> 25:32.708
What's your name?

25:32.708 --> 25:33.500
I'm Joey.

25:33.500 --> 25:34.792
It's nice to meet you, Joey.

25:35.667 --> 25:37.291
I'm Grace.
[CHUCKLES]

25:37.291 --> 25:39.917
And this little pain
in the butt is Sammy.

25:41.166 --> 25:44.041
Guys' names for girls.
That's cute.

25:44.875 --> 25:46.375
You sound like her father.

25:50.917 --> 25:52.208
So, is he gonna be okay?

25:54.250 --> 25:59.041
I don't know. He's in surgery.
Car accident or something.

25:59.041 --> 26:00.792
They won't give me
all the details.

26:01.542 --> 26:03.417
We're not together.

26:04.792 --> 26:07.917
Well, I hope everything
turns out okay.

26:08.333 --> 26:09.375
So, um...

26:10.959 --> 26:12.917
What brings you
to this special place

26:12.917 --> 26:13.959
in the middle of the night?

26:15.750 --> 26:18.750
Uh...I got mugged, actually.

26:19.000 --> 26:20.166
Are you okay?

26:20.166 --> 26:21.750
Oh, I guess so.

26:21.750 --> 26:23.000
I'm still a little shook up.

26:23.417 --> 26:26.583
I can imagine.
I'm-I'm sorry, Joey.

26:26.583 --> 26:27.750
That must've been horrible.

26:28.417 --> 26:30.291
Yeah, it pretty much sucked.
[CHUCKLES]

26:31.417 --> 26:34.500
Well, at least you're alive
to tell the tale, right?

26:35.041 --> 26:36.250
That's true.

26:40.917 --> 26:42.542
So, tell me
about your husband.

26:43.458 --> 26:45.250
[SIGHS]
He's...

26:46.375 --> 26:47.750
What you'd call a loser.

26:48.708 --> 26:49.583
Sorry.

26:49.583 --> 26:51.625
[LAUGHS]
He wasn't always that way.

26:51.917 --> 26:53.417
We just got married
way too young.

26:53.417 --> 26:55.375
Hadn't figured out
who we were yet.

26:55.375 --> 26:57.417
You know, long story.
Blah, blah, blah.

26:57.917 --> 26:59.083
Are you in school?

26:59.083 --> 27:00.625
-Yeah.
-Good for you.

27:00.917 --> 27:01.917
Keep it that way.

27:02.750 --> 27:04.625
I dropped out to follow him
to the city.

27:05.041 --> 27:07.959
He was gonna be Kurt Cobain,
and I was gonna be his Courtney.

27:08.208 --> 27:10.333
[LAUGHS]
[SIGHS]

27:10.333 --> 27:12.625
Didn't quite work out that way.

27:13.583 --> 27:16.917
Worst part is, this little one
loves him to death.

27:19.083 --> 27:20.625
Little girls and their daddies.

27:21.000 --> 27:22.375
Breaks my heart.
[CHUCKLES]

27:24.458 --> 27:27.792
I finally kick the creep out
a month ago.

27:28.125 --> 27:30.166
We finally have
some peace in our lives,

27:30.166 --> 27:31.625
and she wakes up crying for him

27:31.625 --> 27:34.125
in the middle
of every damn night.

27:35.041 --> 27:37.625
I mean, how do you look
in those big blue eyes

27:37.625 --> 27:40.166
and tell her she's better off
without her father?

27:41.458 --> 27:42.542
Well, is there any chance

27:42.542 --> 27:43.959
that you two
will work things out?

27:43.959 --> 27:45.959
[CHUCKLES]
Yeah, maybe...

27:46.417 --> 27:47.667
If you know a couples therapist

27:47.667 --> 27:51.625
that specializes in liars,
thieves, and junkies.

27:52.667 --> 27:56.208
I'm sorry. This is so
not your problem.

27:56.208 --> 27:59.708
No. Hey, I, I asked.

28:04.125 --> 28:08.208
This guy who mugged you,
did he get away?

28:09.166 --> 28:10.083
Uh...

28:11.166 --> 28:12.500
Not exactly, no.

28:12.959 --> 28:13.917
Did they catch him?

28:16.667 --> 28:17.875
Uh, he, uh...

28:19.166 --> 28:20.542
He held me up at gunpoint.

28:20.542 --> 28:23.750
Um, he emptied my bank account,

28:24.000 --> 28:26.959
stole my jacket,
and said good-bye.

28:28.708 --> 28:30.792
But as he was
crossing the street,

28:30.792 --> 28:34.208
um...he was
hit by a car.

28:35.250 --> 28:37.708
Wow. How's that for justice?

28:44.083 --> 28:45.291
Where did this happen?

28:47.458 --> 28:48.625
Downtown Crossing.

28:56.041 --> 28:57.291
Of course.

29:00.125 --> 29:02.208
I think I owe you
an apology, Joey.

29:03.375 --> 29:04.792
I think the scumbag
who mugged you

29:04.792 --> 29:06.667
was probably my husband.

29:08.333 --> 29:09.834
Well, if it makes you
feel any better,

29:09.834 --> 29:10.708
he was...

29:11.250 --> 29:12.417
He was nice about it.

29:12.417 --> 29:13.417
[LAUGHS]
Great.

29:14.000 --> 29:15.750
Maybe they can put that
on his headstone.

29:16.083 --> 29:17.375
That he was nice about it.

29:17.834 --> 29:19.333
He screwed up
his daughter's life,

29:19.333 --> 29:21.166
but he was really nice about it.

29:22.000 --> 29:24.792
[SIGHS]
I think I'm about done here.

29:27.083 --> 29:28.208
You're not gonna stay?

29:28.208 --> 29:30.959
No! Why the hell would I?

29:31.291 --> 29:32.333
To see how he is.

29:32.333 --> 29:35.083
[SIGHS]
I don't care anymore.

29:36.417 --> 29:39.125
Whether he lives or dies,
what difference does it make

29:39.125 --> 29:40.458
to me at this point?

29:41.208 --> 29:42.250
For her sake.

29:42.250 --> 29:45.583
Trust me.
She is better off without him.

29:47.708 --> 29:48.458
[SIGHS]

29:48.750 --> 29:50.500
Look, I'm sorry
about everything.

29:51.250 --> 29:53.500
I wish there was something
I could say or do

29:53.500 --> 29:55.333
to take away what
happened to you tonight,

29:55.333 --> 29:56.333
but I can't.

29:57.708 --> 30:00.083
So, please, let's just
move on, okay?

30:00.083 --> 30:00.917
Look, I'm sorry.

30:01.458 --> 30:02.667
I know this is
none of my business,

30:02.667 --> 30:04.708
but for some reason,
I somehow feel like it is,

30:04.708 --> 30:06.166
and so I'm just
gonna say it.

30:08.041 --> 30:09.291
I've been that little girl.

30:10.959 --> 30:12.750
She doesn't know
her dad's a loser.

30:13.792 --> 30:15.667
She thinks he's pretty much
the greatest thing

30:15.667 --> 30:17.041
in the entire world,

30:17.708 --> 30:19.667
so if things don't go
exactly his way tonight,

30:19.667 --> 30:22.000
wouldn't you like
to give her the chance to--

30:22.000 --> 30:23.166
To what?

30:25.708 --> 30:26.708
To say goodbye?

30:28.834 --> 30:30.458
You're right about
one thing, Joey.

30:32.041 --> 30:33.458
This is none of your business.

30:39.542 --> 30:41.000
Well, hey. What are you
still doing here?

30:41.000 --> 30:42.083
Uh, good question.

30:42.083 --> 30:44.500
Um, if you're looking
for his wife, she just--

30:44.500 --> 30:45.834
Nope. You, actually.

30:46.375 --> 30:47.375
He's asking for you.

30:48.417 --> 30:51.458
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

30:53.959 --> 30:56.500
[PHONES RINGING]
This guy's in bad shape.

30:56.875 --> 30:58.542
That car banged him up
pretty good.

30:59.041 --> 31:01.458
You know what
a sucking chest wound is?

31:02.959 --> 31:04.000
Nah, never mind.

31:04.667 --> 31:07.083
We did what we could.
Now we're just waiting to see

31:07.083 --> 31:08.291
if he needs more surgery.

31:09.166 --> 31:11.375
[MACHINES BEEPING]

31:12.625 --> 31:14.792
You're well aware you don't have
to do this, right?

31:15.750 --> 31:19.041
[MACHINES BEEPING]

31:20.083 --> 31:22.000
[PHONES RINGING]

31:22.875 --> 31:25.375
[MACHINES BEEPING]

31:38.583 --> 31:40.625
[COUGHS]

31:44.291 --> 31:46.333
[SIGHS]
How do I look?

31:47.458 --> 31:49.875
Pretty bad. Hideous, actually.

31:49.875 --> 31:51.917
[LAUGHS]
[COUGHS]

31:53.291 --> 31:55.000
You know, I'd say
I'm sorry to you,

31:55.000 --> 31:55.959
but, uh...

31:55.959 --> 31:57.041
Yeah, what's the point?

31:57.583 --> 31:59.208
It's not like I'd
forgive you or anything.

32:00.417 --> 32:01.625
Fair enough.

32:03.917 --> 32:04.834
I met your family.

32:06.000 --> 32:07.500
-They're here?
-They were.

32:08.083 --> 32:10.458
Your wife and I got talking.
She left.

32:13.458 --> 32:14.625
That's my Gracie.

32:15.750 --> 32:19.000
Your daughter is, uh,
really beautiful.

32:21.083 --> 32:22.458
It's a shame she has
such a dickhead

32:22.458 --> 32:23.500
for a dad.

32:24.166 --> 32:27.041
Well, sounds like your dad
was a bit of a dickhead, too.

32:27.667 --> 32:28.917
Look how well you turned out.

32:29.250 --> 32:30.750
You don't know
anything about me.

32:31.166 --> 32:33.166
True, but from
what I can tell,

32:33.166 --> 32:35.166
you're pretty smart...

32:36.375 --> 32:37.333
And funny...

32:37.917 --> 32:38.959
reasonably hot,

32:39.792 --> 32:41.000
and I imagine most
of your friends

32:41.000 --> 32:42.375
like having you around...

32:43.041 --> 32:43.959
Most of the time,

32:44.333 --> 32:45.375
when you're not
smartin' off with

32:45.625 --> 32:47.083
-that little mouth of yours--
-What do you want?

32:47.083 --> 32:48.125
[LAUGHS]
[COUGHS]

32:48.125 --> 32:49.417
I mean, you asked me
to come in here.

32:49.417 --> 32:50.291
What do you want?

32:50.708 --> 32:51.542
[SIGHS]

32:52.542 --> 32:54.291
Well, you asked me why.

32:55.333 --> 32:56.333
I wanna tell you.

32:56.708 --> 32:57.542
Why what?

32:58.208 --> 33:00.166
Why, with all the good things
in this life,

33:00.166 --> 33:01.917
your father
would choose the bad?

33:03.708 --> 33:05.333
I mean, I figure
it's the least thing I can do

33:05.333 --> 33:08.542
for shoving that gun
in your face tonight.

33:09.917 --> 33:10.792
I'm listening.

33:14.000 --> 33:16.083
You wanna know why I needed
that money so bad?

33:17.750 --> 33:19.125
A couple of weeks ago,

33:19.875 --> 33:22.041
Gracie let me
walk Sammy to school.

33:23.166 --> 33:25.000
[CHUCKLES]
Why the hell she did,

33:25.000 --> 33:26.083
I have no idea.

33:27.000 --> 33:28.708
Must have been
a moment of weakness.

33:30.708 --> 33:32.333
She gave me 500 bucks

33:32.959 --> 33:34.333
to pay for her day-care.

33:36.458 --> 33:37.458
What do I do?

33:38.583 --> 33:40.333
Drop my daughter
off at school and...

33:41.667 --> 33:43.333
spend the money on dope.

33:45.333 --> 33:48.083
Heartwarming story.
What's your point?

33:48.542 --> 33:51.375
Well, the point is,
I love my wife.

33:51.750 --> 33:53.041
I love my daughter,

33:54.291 --> 33:55.417
but...

33:57.333 --> 33:58.542
I am who I am.

33:59.667 --> 34:01.083
Nothing's gonna change that.

34:03.000 --> 34:05.333
I mean, you wanna know
why people do the things

34:05.333 --> 34:06.500
that they do.

34:06.500 --> 34:07.417
[CHUCKLES]

34:07.417 --> 34:09.291
There is no why,
sweetheart.

34:10.667 --> 34:11.708
They just do.

34:11.708 --> 34:12.583
That's crap.

34:13.708 --> 34:14.750
If you really loved
your daughter,

34:15.041 --> 34:17.291
if you really loved her,
you wouldn't do those things.

34:17.291 --> 34:19.792
No, you're wrong.
I do love my daughter.

34:19.792 --> 34:20.750
[SCOFFS]

34:21.000 --> 34:22.250
I love her very much.

34:23.041 --> 34:26.208
I love her so much
it's easier just being stoned.

34:27.333 --> 34:29.041
You know, it's not
like I can overcome

34:29.041 --> 34:30.625
every tragic flaw I have.

34:30.625 --> 34:32.333
It's just not possible,
you know?

34:32.792 --> 34:33.958
So, let me ask you a question.

34:34.625 --> 34:36.375
She comes to you
in 15 years and asks you

34:36.375 --> 34:38.083
why you couldn't get
over yourself for her,

34:38.083 --> 34:39.250
and what do you say?

34:39.250 --> 34:40.375
Grow up.

34:41.041 --> 34:42.208
Get on with your life.

34:43.792 --> 34:44.875
Don't blame me.

34:44.875 --> 34:46.000
[CHUCKLES]
[COUGHS]

34:49.917 --> 34:52.208
I really admire
that tough-guy bravado.

34:54.750 --> 34:56.417
You know what?
it just doesn't track.

34:58.417 --> 34:59.583
I mean, you obviously
cared enough

34:59.583 --> 35:01.166
to want to get that money back.

35:03.625 --> 35:05.834
And now it looks like
you're gonna die alone.

35:06.750 --> 35:07.750
How does that feel?

35:08.166 --> 35:10.583
[COUGHS]
Big deal.

35:11.542 --> 35:13.041
Everybody dies alone.

35:17.458 --> 35:18.708
Great. Good answer.

35:19.166 --> 35:20.417
Well, I'll let you get to it.

35:21.041 --> 35:23.375
-You have a nice afterlife.
-Hey.

35:29.000 --> 35:30.583
Do you think
she'll ever forgive me?

35:33.250 --> 35:34.333
Your daughter?

35:36.625 --> 35:37.625
Yeah.

35:37.625 --> 35:39.417
[DISTANT SIRENS]

35:48.208 --> 35:51.458
[LABORED BREATHING]

36:01.083 --> 36:04.875
My tenth birthday,
my father takes me to the park,

36:05.333 --> 36:07.375
and if you knew Mike Potter,

36:07.375 --> 36:08.834
you'd know that was
a pretty big deal.

36:08.834 --> 36:10.750
I mean, he never
really had time

36:10.750 --> 36:11.792
for stuff like that.

36:13.667 --> 36:17.166
But he took me, and
we played for hours.

36:17.667 --> 36:20.250
Jungle gym, swings, everything.

36:21.750 --> 36:23.291
And I was so happy.

36:25.542 --> 36:28.375
He was so popular
with the people there, and...

36:29.250 --> 36:30.875
Everyone seemed
to know him, and...

36:32.917 --> 36:34.917
I was so proud
to be his daughter.

36:37.125 --> 36:39.375
I mean, he was, like,
the mayor or something, and...

36:42.208 --> 36:43.375
It wasn't until years later

36:43.375 --> 36:45.583
that I realized he was
dealing drugs to them.

36:48.125 --> 36:49.500
Heartwarming story.

36:51.083 --> 36:52.041
What's your  point?

36:56.708 --> 36:57.667
My point is...

37:01.375 --> 37:03.250
My dad did a lot
of crappy stuff.

37:04.875 --> 37:06.583
I mean, this is the guy
who cheated on my mom

37:06.583 --> 37:09.208
with a cocktail waitress
while she was dying of cancer.

37:10.875 --> 37:12.417
He let me and my sister down

37:13.208 --> 37:14.125
time and time again,

37:14.125 --> 37:16.000
so many times
and in so many ways,

37:16.000 --> 37:17.792
it became funny.

37:20.875 --> 37:21.917
But you know what?

37:27.041 --> 37:28.458
That day at the park...

37:30.917 --> 37:34.208
It still goes down in the books
as my favorite day ever.

37:35.417 --> 37:36.417
Oh, yeah?

37:38.917 --> 37:40.000
Yeah.

37:40.917 --> 37:42.917
[LAUGHS WEAKLY]

37:47.917 --> 37:51.375
[MACHINE FLATLINES]

38:01.041 --> 38:02.208
[DOOR OPENS]

38:04.250 --> 38:07.834
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

38:14.959 --> 38:19.917
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

38:23.834 --> 38:24.875
[SIGHS]

38:36.750 --> 38:37.792
[SNIFFLES]

38:43.333 --> 38:44.458
Hey, sweetie.

38:45.959 --> 38:49.959
Did my daddy do
something bad to you?

38:52.458 --> 38:53.333
No.

38:54.500 --> 38:56.417
He did something
really nice for me.

38:57.333 --> 38:58.291
He did?

38:58.959 --> 38:59.917
Yeah.

39:01.166 --> 39:03.583
I was crossing the street,

39:03.583 --> 39:06.417
and I wasn't paying
any attention,

39:07.166 --> 39:09.041
and there was this car coming,
and it was gonna hit me,

39:09.041 --> 39:12.166
but then your daddy came out
and pushed me out of the way.

39:15.166 --> 39:16.667
He saved my life tonight.

39:16.667 --> 39:19.000
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

39:20.583 --> 39:24.500
Did you hear that, mama?
Daddy's a hero.

39:25.291 --> 39:26.125
[LAUGHS]

39:27.625 --> 39:30.667
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

39:30.667 --> 39:32.375
[MOUTHING]
Thank you.

39:36.208 --> 39:39.875
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

39:48.208 --> 39:49.750
[SNIFFLES]

39:51.250 --> 39:54.375
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

